@startuml C4 Code Level - ML Training Pipeline
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam classBackgroundColor #F0F0F0
skinparam arrowColor #333333
skinparam classBorderColor #333333

title C4 Code Level: ML Training Pipeline\n(airflow_pipeline/dags/train_pipeline.py)

package "train_pipeline.py" {

    package "Configuration" {
        class CLASS_NAMES {
            + [str]: beauty_salon, drugstore, restaurant, movie_theater, apartment_building, supermarket
            + CLASS_NAME_TO_INDEX: Dict[str, int]
            + MIN_REVIEWED_FOR_RETRAIN: int
            + MLRUNS_CONTAINER_DIR: Path
            + MLRUNS_HOST_DIR: Path
        }
    }

    package "Feature Extraction (Task 1)" {
        class extract_features_task {
            + {static} extract_features_task()
            --
            - load BackboneModel (ResNet34, EfficientNetV2-S)
            - load HF dataset: train_v1, train_v2, test
            - apply transform: Resize(224), ToTensor, Normalize
            - extract features via backbone → memmap .npy files
            - extract reviewed production samples
        }

        class _load_reviewed_rows {
            + {static} _load_reviewed_rows(transform, device): (Tensor, ndarray)
            --
            - query prediction_logs: WHERE review_status IN ('approved', 'rejected')
            - MIN_REVIEWED_FOR_RETRAIN gate: return (None, None) if below
            - decode image_bytes → PIL → transform
            - map final_class → label via CLASS_NAME_TO_INDEX
        }

        class _extract_reviewed_features {
            + {static} _extract_reviewed_features(model, x_tensor, batch_size, use_half): ndarray
            --
            - batch inference via backbone.inference_mode()
            - concatenate batches → float32 numpy array
        }
    }

    package "Model Training (Task 2)" {
        class train_and_log_task {
            + {static} train_and_log_task()
            --
            - load extracted features from .npy files (train_v1, train_v2, test)
            - 4-way grid: (ResNet34, EfficientNetV2-S) × (train_v1, train_v2)
            - for each config:
              * augment with reviewed samples via _augment_with_reviewed
              * fit PCA(256), then LogisticRegression
              * compute train/test accuracy, macro-F1
              * log to MLflow
            - track best_f1, best_record (ModelInfo)
            - promote winning model via current_model.json
        }

        class _augment_with_reviewed {
            + {static} _augment_with_reviewed(X_train, y_train, data_dir, reviewed_feat_file): (ndarray, ndarray, int)
            --
            - load X_reviewed_*.npy and y_reviewed.npy
            - concatenate to X_train/y_train
            - return augmented arrays + count
        }

        class _resolve_pkl_path {
            + {static} _resolve_pkl_path(model_info): str | None
            --
            - extract ModelInfo.model_id (MLflow 3 layout)
            - query MLflow run for experiment_id
            - compute HOST-relative path: MLRUNS_HOST_DIR / exp_id / models / model_id / artifacts / model.pkl
            - fallback to MLflow 2 artifact_uri parsing
        }
    }

    package "Baseline Regeneration (Task 3)" {
        class regenerate_baseline_task {
            + {static} regenerate_baseline_task()
            --
            - delete baseline_reference.json if exists
            - next drift DAG run will re-bootstrap from post-retrain predictions
        }
    }

    package "DAG Orchestration" {
        class DAG_model_training_pipeline {
            + schedule: None (trigger-only)
            + description: Training pipeline comparing ResNet34 and EfficientNetV2-S
            --
            + extract_task: PythonOperator(extract_features_task)
            + train_log_task: PythonOperator(train_and_log_task)
            + regenerate_baseline: PythonOperator(regenerate_baseline_task)
            + dependencies: extract_task >> train_log_task >> regenerate_baseline
        }
    }

    package "Dependencies" {
        class PREDICTIONS_DATABASE {
            + url: postgresql://predictions:predictions@predictions-db:5432/predictions
            + schema: prediction_logs (image_bytes, final_class, review_status)
        }

        class MLFLOW_TRACKING {
            + uri: http://mlflow:5000
            + experiment: Places365_Classification
            + artifacts: mlruns/*/models/*/artifacts/model.pkl
        }

        class HF_DATASET {
            + source: Punnarunwuwu/seml-industry-ver
            + splits: train_v1, train_v2, test
        }

        class PYTORCH_MODELS {
            + ResNet34: torchvision.models.resnet34(weights=ResNet34_Weights.DEFAULT)
            + EfficientNetV2-S: torchvision.models.efficientnet_v2_s(weights=EfficientNet_V2_S_Weights.DEFAULT)
        }

        class SKLEARN_MODELS {
            + PCA: sklearn.decomposition.PCA(n_components=256)
            + LogisticRegression: sklearn.linear_model.LogisticRegression(max_iter=2000, n_jobs=-1, C=1.0)
        }
    }
}

' Relationships
extract_features_task --> _load_reviewed_rows: uses
extract_features_task --> _extract_reviewed_features: uses
extract_features_task --> HF_DATASET: loads
extract_features_task --> PYTORCH_MODELS: backbone

train_and_log_task --> _augment_with_reviewed: uses
train_and_log_task --> _resolve_pkl_path: uses
train_and_log_task --> SKLEARN_MODELS: fits
train_and_log_task --> MLFLOW_TRACKING: logs artifacts, ModelInfo
train_and_log_task --> PREDICTIONS_DATABASE: writes current_model.json pointer

_load_reviewed_rows --> PREDICTIONS_DATABASE: query reviewed rows
_augment_with_reviewed --> PREDICTIONS_DATABASE: depends on extracted features

regenerate_baseline_task --> MLFLOW_TRACKING: cleanup (baseline_reference.json)

DAG_model_training_pipeline --> extract_features_task: orchestrates
DAG_model_training_pipeline --> train_and_log_task: orchestrates
DAG_model_training_pipeline --> regenerate_baseline_task: orchestrates

note right of train_and_log_task
    Produces current_model.json at:
    airflow_pipeline/mlruns/current_model.json
    with keys: {pca_pkl_path, clf_pkl_path, run_id, winning_config, test_f1, promoted_at}

    This pointer is read by api/main.py:load_model_pointer()
end note

note bottom of _augment_with_reviewed
    Gate: MIN_REVIEWED_FOR_RETRAIN (default 10)
    If fewer than 10 reviewed rows exist,
    retraining uses only HF data
end note

@enduml
